text: Francis Alphonso “Frank” Collins (September 28, 1901 - November 9, 1940) was a Canadian ice hockey player. Collins won a silver medal with the Canada men's national ice hockey team, coached by Harold Ballard, at the 1933 World Ice Hockey Championships held in Prague, Czechoslovakia.http://www.azhockey.com/squads/squadscanada.html ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1901 births Category:1940 deaths Category:Canadian ice hockey right wingers
